n part this may be a transferred use of the surname derived from the medieval given name. <i>Piers</i> was revived in the mid-20th century, perhaps partly under the influence of  William Langland's  great rambling medieval poem Piers Plowman (  1367–86 ), in which the character of Piers symbolizes the virtues of hard work, honesty, and fairness."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Piers d'Oyré was born in 1244, in Drayton, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom as the son of Robert d'Oyré. He had at least 1 daughter. He died in 1303, in Oyré, Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1244–1303":"1244–1303","1235–1299":"1235–1299","1211–1270":"1211–1270","1303":"1303","1235":"1235","1244":"1244","1211":"1211","1299":"1299","1270":"1270","Oyré, Châtellerault, Vienne, Aquitaine":"Oyré, Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa","Drayton, Hellesden, Norfolk, England":"Drayton, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1244–1303":"1244–1303","1235–1299":"1235–1299","1211–1270":"1211–1270","1303":"1303","1235":"1235","1244":"1244","1211":"1211","1299":"1299","1270":"1270","Oyré, Châtellerault, Vienne, Aquitaine":"Oyré, Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Ranska","Drayton, Hellesden, Norfolk, England":"Drayton, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1244–1303":"1244–1303","1235–1299":"1235–1299","1211–1270":"1211–1270","1303":"1303","1235":"1235","1244":"1244","1211":"1211","1299":"1299","1270":"1270","Oyré, Châtellerault, Vienne, Aquitaine":"Oyré, Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France","Drayton, Hellesden, Norfolk, England":"Drayton, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Piers d'Oyré est né en 1244, à Drayton, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de Robert d'Oyré. Il a eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1303, à Oyré, Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France, à l’âge de 59 ans."},"de":{"1244–1303":"1244–1303","1235–1299":"1235–1299","1211–1270":"1211–1270","1303":"1303","1235":"1235","1244":"1244","1211":"1211","1299":"1299","1270":"1270","Oyré, Ch